Characteristics[NumberOfSamples]: 111 lymph node metastasis samples from patients with malignant melanoma (Stage 3 and 4), archived in the local malignant melanoma biobank were obtained from Skåne University Hospital, Sweden.
Characteristics[Specimen]: Frozen tissue samples from BD20 were sectioned on a cryostat into 10 µm thick slices (approximately 6×6 mm), placed into a 96 well plate and stored at −80 °C until further use.
Characteristics[MaterialType]: Frozen specimens (snap frozen immediately after surgery)
Characteristics[SpikedCompound]: The samples were spiked with 0.1 mg of internal standard – chicken lysozyme (CL, Swiss-Prot accession no. P00698).
20 µL of samples were mixed with 20 µL of peptide retention time calibration mixture (PRTC, Pierce/Thermo Scientific, Rockford, IL, 20 fmoL/mL).
Comment[Instrument]: Thermo Easy nLC 1000 system (Thermo Fisher Scientific)
Q-Exactive Plus mass spectrometer (Thermo Scientific, San José, CA)
Comment[Separation]: Online chromatography was performed with a Thermo Easy nLC 1000 system (Thermo Fisher Scientific) coupled online to a Q-Exactive Plus mass spectrometer (Thermo Scientific, San José, CA).
Comment[FlowRateChromatogram]: Flow rate of 300 nL/min and a column temperature of 35 °C were utilised.
Comment[GradientTime]: the gradient went from 5% to 40% B in the first 120 min
Comment[FragmentationMethod]: fragmented in the HCD collision cell
Comment[MS2MassAnalyzer]: tandem mass spectra were acquired in the Orbitrap mass analyzer with resolution of 17 500 (at m/z 200), target AGC value of 1−106 and maximum injection time of 120 ms.
Comment[NumberOfMissedCleavages]: Up to two missed cleavages for tryptic peptides was allowed.
Comment[Instrument]: Thermo Easy nLC 1000 system (Thermo Fisher Scientific)
Q-Exactive Plus mass spectrometer (Thermo Scientific, San José, CA)

Characteristics[MaterialType]: Frozen specimens (snap frozen immediately after surgery)
Characteristics[SpikedCompound]: The samples were spiked with 0.1 mg of internal standard – chicken lysozyme (CL, Swiss-Prot accession no. P00698).
20 µL of samples were mixed with 20 µL of peptide retention time calibration mixture (PRTC, Pierce/Thermo Scientific, Rockford, IL, 20 fmoL/mL).
Comment[Instrument]: Thermo Easy nLC 1000 system (Thermo Fisher Scientific)
Q-Exactive Plus mass spectrometer (Thermo Scientific, San José, CA)
Comment[Separation]: Online chromatography was performed with a Thermo Easy nLC 1000 system (Thermo Fisher Scientific) coupled online to a Q-Exactive Plus mass spectrometer (Thermo Scientific, San José, CA).
Comment[FlowRateChromatogram]: Flow rate of 300 nL/min and a column temperature of 35 °C were utilised.
Comment[GradientTime]: the gradient went from 5% to 40% B in the first 120 min
Comment[FragmentationMethod]: fragmented in the HCD collision cell
Comment[MS2MassAnalyzer]: tandem mass spectra were acquired in the Orbitrap mass analyzer with resolution of 17 500 (at m/z 200), target AGC value of 1−106 and maximum injection time of 120 ms.
Comment[NumberOfMissedCleavages]: Up to two missed cleavages for tryptic peptides was allowed.
